HEADWORD: Cortes
<hw>Cor"tes</hw> <pr>(k⟦ocir⟧r"t⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[Sp. & Pg., fr. <ets>corte</ets> court.]</ety> <def>The legislative
assembly, composed of nobility, clergy, and representatives of cities,
which in Spain and in Portugal answers, in some measure, to the
Parliament of Great Britain.</def>⟦br⟧
